Extract the 'y' axis value of the last line segment in the provided 2-d sketch.



```kcl
lastSegY(sketch: [Sketch](/docs/kcl/types/Sketch)): [number](/docs/kcl/types/number)
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `sketch` | [`Sketch`](/docs/kcl/types/Sketch) | The sketch whose line segment is being queried | Yes |

### Returns

[`number`](/docs/kcl/types/number)


### Examples

```kcl
exampleSketch = startSketchOn(XZ)
  |> startProfile(at = [0, 0])
  |> line(end = [5, 0])
  |> line(end = [20, 5])
  |> line(end = [0, lastSegY(%)])
  |> line(end = [-15, 0])
  |> close()

example = extrude(exampleSketch, length = 5)
```
